hopobject.body: Children with disabilities nexgen pharma australia For all of 2009, Pimco's Total Return Fund posted a return of 13.83 percent. It was thefund's best showing in a decade, beating the Barclays U.S. Aggregate Bond Index by nearly eightpercentage points - its widest spread over the benchmark, according to Morningstar, since 1988,the fund's first full year of operation. By far the biggest contributor - at 4.15 percentagepoints - was the fund's bet on mortgage bonds of all types, according to a confidentialbreakdown of the fund's returns obtained by Reuters.
